âI wonât have you go out,â she cried, feigning sudden despair. âI wonât
let you leave my side. Those scoundrels will kill you.â

The commander stopped in amazement.

âHang it all!â he growled, âif the women are going to whine now--Come
along, Rougon!â

âNo, no,â continued the old woman, affecting increase of terror, âhe
shaânât follow you. I will hang on to his clothes and prevent him.â

The marquis, very much surprised at the scene, looked inquiringly at
