You are rushing into the cannonâs mouth to no purpose.â

âEh! that is our duty,â said Sicardot, impatiently.

Felicite burst into sobs.

âIf they donât kill him, theyâll make him a prisoner,â she continued,
looked fixedly at her husband. âGood heavens! What will become of me,
left alone in an abandoned town?â

âBut,â exclaimed the commander, âwe shall be arrested just the same if
