âAnd you were only forty-one; itâs marvellous!â

âAh, indeed! it must have been frightfully dark!â

âNo; I confess I never should have dared it!â

âThen you seized him, like that, by the throat?

âAnd the insurgents, what did they say?â

These remarks and questions only incited Rougonâs imagination the more.
He replied to everybody. He mimicked the action. This stout man, in his
