She suppressed a smile, and began to feel some pity for the poor man.

âWell,â he said anxiously, when he had finished, ânow you know
everything. Do you see any means of saving us from ruin!â

She still gave no answer. She appeared to be pondering deeply.

âYou are an intelligent woman,â he continued, in order to flatter her,
âI did wrong in keeping any secret from you; I see it now.â

âLet us say nothing more about that,â she replied. âIn my opinion, if
you had enough courage----â And as he looked at her eagerly, she broke
