âBut what could she have seen?â asked Rougon, at last venturing to quit
the corner where he had hidden himself.

âI have a terrible suspicion,â Pascal replied. âI was going to speak to
you about Silvere when you came in. He is a prisoner. You must endeavour
to obtain his release from the prefect, if there is still time.â

The old oil-dealer turned pale as he looked at his son. Then, rapidly,
he responded: âListen to me; you stay here and watch her. Iâm too busy
